Fabless Semiconductor Firm Xemics Closes $6M Round Three	  mail <http://alert.venturewire.com/o_mailer.asp?sid=LJQOKHLNII>  	
NEUCHATEL, SWITZERLAND -- Xemics, a developer of fabless semiconductors for short-range wireless connectivity, said it has closed $6 million in a third round of funding. New money will be used for product development and marketing in the U.S. and the Far East. [more.. <http://professional.venturewire.com/prostory.asp>]
